reviews.review_text: A sweet show! This was my 4th Grateful Dead concert, and the second one to really stick with me in terms of remembering what they played & how good it was. Terrific playing throughout, though Jerry is lyrically forgetful & vocally scratchy at times. Unusual set list in second set: Ship of Fools & He's Gone back to back, & it was these 2 songs that I remembered most, for both were rendered with style & a LOT of soul. Some said it was the worst of the year? Huh! Well, I didn't see the whole year, but I saw this show & the 2 before it, & I'm very, very happy I did. The first night was better, but not by much!

worst soundboard ever! This is probably the worst soundboard ever.   Is this poor quality even possible?

Don't misconstrue. I appreciate all this stuff.  This is an observation.
